window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>With translations into 15 languages, renowned author L.M. Montgomery penned some 500 short stories and poems as well as the classic <i>Anne of Green Gables</i> novels.</p> <p>Rilla Blythe, youngest daughter of Anne, is almost 15 in 1914. As her brothers and friends prepare to go off to battle, the irrepressible Rilla realizes that she will be changed forever and the world will never be the same.</p> <p> Narrator Barbara Caruso presents a poignant delivery of this family classic.</p>"; 
